name: Zucchini Pancakes
author: William Anatooskin
summary: An easy recipe to make.  A delicious vegetable pancake for breakfast, brunch, lunch or just a snack.
directions: Preheat grill to 425 to 450 degrees F (220 to 225 degrees C)
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, add shredded zucchini and mix well using a fork
Add flour, sugar, salt and vegetable oil and stir to blend well
Finally, add baking powder and mix well using a  large spoon
The batter's consistency should be like heavy whipping cream
Spoon batter on hot grill (about 2 tablespoons) for each pancake
Cook until there are no longer bubbles forming in  the pancake about 2 minutes; turn over and cook for 2 minutes longer
Rub pancakes with melted butter and serve immediately
